replies.body:
I'm having a similar problem. I recently had an issue with my computer with a new installation for lol, I clicked Okay, and accept for the update to do its thing but it would just close out. This is where it all started (around 10 days ago). I researched a lot and got the common "reinstall lol" or "get the hex tech repair tool", so I reinstalled lol and begun the reinstallation and re patching process with the hex tech tool, but when I finally downloaded the LolpatcherUx, it comes up in large writing that "the client update has begun", and when I click launch the window closes and does not reopen. I am really confused because it has old image of the L icon for lol and also keeps explaining what Awesome things are in the new client (showing the new L icon)… But I have had the new client for ages, and these updates seemed as if they happened a while ago. 

Did I just download an outdated lol? or is that just the process of downloading lol, such as downloading the old lol and having to update to the new client regardless if I already had it before I uninstalled lol. I've had many other issues leading up to this one, and have solved them myself, but I cannot figure out a way to make this damn game WORK!
{{summoner:3}}
